o` for edges. But `upsert.cjs` (via the `deep_research_auto.yaml:1057-1058` reducer map) validates node `kind` against `VALID_KINDS.research=[QUESTION,FINDING,CLAIM,SOURCE]` and reads edges as `source`/`target`/`relation` — so `{type:node, label:\"question\"}` → kind `\"\"`/`NODE` (rejected) and `{from,to,label}` → missing sourceId/targetId (rejected). Verified with the real failing packet `002-code-graph`: its state log emits exactly `{type:node, label:\"baseline|candidate|mapping\"}` + `{type:edge, from, to, label}`. FIX (template-only, no reducer/code change, no schema-design call, does not touch the other session's actively-developed coverage-graph reducer): rewrote the graphEvents contract in BOTH `deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl` and the deep-review sibling to mandate the exact canonical shapes — Node `{type:\"node\",id,kind:<valid enum>,label}` and Edge `{type:\"edge\",id,source,target,relation:<valid enum>}` — enumerating the existing per-loop-type valid vocabularies inline. PROOF: ran both shapes through `upsert.cjs` directly against a throwaway in-repo packet — OLD shape → `insertedNodes:0, insertedEdges:0, graph_upsert_event_count:0` (reproduces the empty-graph symptom); NEW canonical shape → `insertedNodes:2, insertedEdges:1, graph_upsert_...\n  Line 126: - [x] T-0424 Fix missing `convergence.cjs` call in deep-loop YAML workflow before stop logic (0424) — ALREADY_CORRECT, VERIFIED. Confirmed via `git status --short` that no files were touched (a deliberately verify-only redispatch): HEAD already has the `convergence.cjs` call before stop logic in `deep_research_auto.yaml`/`deep_research_confirm.yaml`. The original FAIL was almost certainly reading the OTHER concurrent session's uncommitted working-tree state (per the original caveat), not a gap in shipped code.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/system-speckit/028-memory-search-intelligence/001-release-cleanup/015-manual-playbook-execution-sweep/001-findings-remediation/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 57: The headline late fix is **T-0381** — the `doctor` deep-loop convergence diagnostic returned empty graph signals for qualifying packets. Root cause was traced (not to `convergence.cjs`, which correctly returns empty signals for a 0-node graph, but) to the iteration prompt-pack's under-specified `graphEvents` contract: it never declared a `kind` field or the canonical edge fields, so executors emitted `{type:\"node\",label:\"question\"}` and `{from,to,label}` edges that the reducer (`upsert.cjs` via the `deep_research_auto.yaml` reducer map) silently rejected — every event dropped, graph empty, signals empty.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/checklists/command_authoring.md:\n  Line 40: - [ ] For contract-renderer commands, verify the rendered contract source such as `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md` and workflow assets such as `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:\n  Line 364:     autoWorkflowPath: '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml',\n\n  Line 373:       '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml',\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/system-speckit/028-memory-search-intelligence/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:\n  Line 14: 4. `/deep:research` has an asymmetry: startup context loading calls `memory_context` and defines `if_context_found`/`if_no_context`, but the inspected startup block lacks the later loop's explicit MCP error/timeout fallback