{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784314517572,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c8ffeulTMP4nVP9BJov","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_u8v4PNh2tNelhQcZXr9HtmEZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":40,"limit":160},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n40: - Treat convergence as telemetry only. A low novelty signal requires a broader unexplored angle, not early synthesis.\n41: - Stop early only for unrecoverable state corruption or three consecutive failed iterations.\n42: \n43: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n44: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n45: [None yet]\n46: \n47: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n48: \n49: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n50: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n51: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n52: - comparing the hub’s explicit defer branch with registry topology and two child fallback patterns separated selection metadata from post-selection guidance, avoiding a repeat of the Run 1 default-policy verdict. (iteration 1)\n53: \n54: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n55: \n56: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n57: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n58: - the optional memory trigger timed out, and source inspection cannot measure whether a card changes live model decisions; the necessary behavioral evidence is absent from committed documents. (iteration 1)\n59: \n60: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n61: \n62: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n63: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n64: ### An unconditional child-specific hint before ranking a candidate: eac