s informational only for this detached lineage.\n- The workflow's normal parent-spec, graph, memory, and continuity operations are intentionally excluded to honor the detached write boundary.\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n\n- Max iterations: 5.\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05, telemetry only.\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls and 10 minutes.\n- Progressive synthesis: true.\n- All writes are limited to this lineage directory.\n- Reducer-owned state is refreshed only through the workflow reducer binding, never by a leaf iteration.","lineStart":40,"lineEnd":133,"totalLines":133,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784314517566,"end":1784314517571}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_06a0c11066223256016a5a7a95737c8191b63321bf8d87f530"}},"id":"prt_f716ed7ee0012IiWbJrrUI31l7","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c8ffeulTMP4nVP9BJov","messageID":"msg_f716eadf9001BOTBvPmxjp6nD6"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784314517586,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c8ffeulTMP4nVP9BJov","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_yP9BKxodQFroXCC6YvHQvphK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/findings-registry.json","offset":120,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/findings-registry.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n120:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n121:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n122:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n123:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n124:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n125:     }\n126:   ],\n127:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n128:   \"carriedForwardOpenQuestions\": [],\n129:   \"uncoveredQuestions\": [\n130:     \"**Q1 (thread 1):** When a null hub defers, what routing-helper payload actually improves live routing: a full mode registry, a compressed disambiguation card, or a child hint? What measurable tradeoff establishes the minimum useful payload?\",\n131:     \"**Q2 (thread 3):** What controlled experiment would distinguish clean model disambiguation from arbitrary mode picking on a null hub, including zero-signal, weak-signal, and adversarially ambiguous requests?\",\n132:     \"**Q3 (thread 4):** What safe migration and rollback sequence could flip proposed defaults while detecting regressions before live routing behavior is broadly affected?\",\n133:     \"**Q4 (thread 8):** How should a hub with two genuinely co-dominant modes behave: ordered bundle, ranked helper, contextual detector, or defer? What evidence rule prevents a false dominant default?\",\n134:     \"**Q5 (thread 10):** If `defaultMode` currently anchors hub identity or catch-all scoring, what exact replacement contracts and benchmark assertions keep a null hub discoverable without recreating hidden auto-default bias?\"\n135:   ],\n136:   \"keyFindings\": [\n137:     {\n138:       \"id\": \"finding-1-4-the-committed-payload-sizes-make-indiscriminate-helper-loading-hard-to-justify-q\",\n139:       \"text\": \"The committed payload sizes make indiscriminate helper loading hard to justify: `quick_reference.md` is 14,132 bytes, the full registry is 10,515 bytes, `hub-router.json` is 5,937 bytes, and the two representative child route maps are 3,942 and 3,804 bytes. The minimum plausible improvement is therefore a newly generated compressed disambiguation card: defer reason; zero to two ranked candidate mode labels with one discriminating alias each; the four hub confirmation fields; and a child hint only for an already-ranked candidate. This is a proposal, not a measured token floor. [SOURCE: command output: wc -c .opencode/skills/sk-doc/{mode-registry.json,hub-router.json,shared/references/quick_reference.md,create-command/references/README.md,create-quality-control/references/README.md}] [INFERENCE: based on the source topology and payload-size comparison above]\",\n140:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n141:       \"sources\": [\n142:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160\",\n143:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n144:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:55-101\",\n145:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9, 207-214\",\n146:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92\",\n147:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:51-124\",\n148:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16, 64-145\",\n149:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:15-38\",\n150:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:15-35\",\n151:         \"command output: `wc -c` payload-size comparison\"\n152:       ]\n153:     },\n154:     {\n155:       \"id\": \"finding-1-1-the-full-mode-registry-json-is-not-a-minimal-null-state-helper-it-carries-all-12\",\n156:       \"text\": \"The full `mode-registry.json` is not a minimal null-state helper: it carries all 12 workflow entries, including packet identity, command, aliases, tool surfaces, and advisor metadata. The hub instead classifies with `hub-router.json`, then resolves the matching registry entry only after a mode is selected. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-95]\",\n157:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n158:       \"sources\": [\n159:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160\",\n160:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n161:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:55-101\",\n162:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9, 207-214\",\n163:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92\",\n164:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:51-124\",\n165:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16, 64-145\",\n166:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:15-38\",\n167:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:15-35\",\n168:         \"command output: `wc -c` payload-size comparison\"\n169:       ]\n170:     },\n171:     {\n172:       \"id\": \"finding-1-2-the-live-null-hub-behavior-already-has-a-small-semantic-contract-with-low-confid\",\n173:       \"text\": \"The live null-hub behavior already has a small *semantic* contract: with low confidence, contradiction, or no winning mode under `defaultMode: null`, it loads `shared/references/quick_reference.md` and asks for workflow mode, target component, inputs, and validation expectations. But the configured default resource is a quality/optimizer cheat sheet, not a cross-mode choice card. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-14] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:77-97] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:64-145]\",\n174:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n175:       \"sources\": [\n176:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160\",\n177:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n178:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:55-101\",\n179:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9, 207-214\",\n180:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92\",\n181:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:51-124\",\n182:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16, 64-145\",\n183:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:15-38\",\n184:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:15-35\",\n185:         \"command output: `wc -c` payload-size comparison\"\n186:       ]\n187:     },\n188:     {\n189:       \"id\": \"finding-1-3-the-second-layer-router-and-representative-children-favor-scoped-on-demand-loadi\",\n190:       \"text\": \"The second-layer router and representative children favor scoped, on-demand loading: no keyword match confirms artifact and intent before loading anything, and full inventory is explicit-only. Child fallbacks first request child-specific discriminators, then load a thin route map that points to one needed concern; this makes a child hint useful only after a candidate child is already ranked. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:207-214] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:69-124] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:21-38] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:21-35]\",\n191:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n192:       \"sources\": [\n193:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160\",\n194:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n195:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:55-101\",\n196:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9, 207-214\",\n197:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92\",\n198:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:51-124\",\n199:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16, 64-145\",\n200:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:15-38\",\n201:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:15-35\",\n202:         \"command output: `wc -c` payload-size comparison\"\n203:       ]\n204:     }\n205:   ],\n206:   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n207:     {\n208:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-3b751ae37ebf\",\n209:       \"text\": \"An unconditional child-specific hint before ranking a candidate: each inspected child asks for information that presupposes its own domain, so it cannot resolve a genuine zero-signal hub request. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:81-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:105-124]\",\n210:       \"contentHash\": \"3b751ae37ebf\",\n211:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n212:     },\n213:     {\n214:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-98b360fee718\",\n215:       \"text\": \"Committed sources provide byte-size proxies, not a token budget or route-accuracy experiment; they cannot establish an exact numerical minimum payload.\",\n216:       \"contentHash\": \"98b360fee718\",\n217:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n218:     },\n219:     {\n220:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-18ffba478699\",\n221:       \"text\": \"The existing shared quick reference is not a neutral fallback-menu specimen, so its size cannot be treated as the target card size. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:64-145]\",\n222:       \"contentHash\": \"18ffba478699\",\n223:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n224:     },\n225:     {\n226:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-d3becd5e13cc\",\n227:       \"text\": \"Unconditional full-registry injection as the null fallback: it includes routing-adjacent metadata and all child surfaces, while the hub contract already separates classification from entry resolution. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-95]\",\n228:       \"contentHash\": \"d3becd5e13cc\",\n229:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n230:     }\n231:   ],\n232:   \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n233:   \"rejectedPatternIndex\": {\n234:     \"maxEntries\": 100,\n235:     \"fuzzyThreshold\": 0.85,\n236:     \"entries\": []\n237:   },\n238:   \"rejectedPatternWarnings\": [],\n239:   \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n240:   \"minIdeaObservations\": 2,\n241:   \"observedIdeas\": [],\n242:   \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n243:   \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n244:   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n245:   \"graphConvergenceScore\": 0,\n246:   \"graphDecision\": null,\n247:   \"graphBlockers\": [],\n248:   \"divergence\": {\n249:     \"started\": [],\n250:     \"completed\": [],\n251:     \"failed\": [],\n252:     \"overrides\": [],\n253:     \"saturatedDirections\": [],\n254:     \"remainingFrontier\": [],\n255:     \"currentFocus\": \"\",\n256:     \"activePivotId\": null,\n257:     \"activeSourceIteration\": null\n258:   },\n259:   \"metrics\": {\n260:     \"iterationsCompleted\": 1,\n261:     \"openQuestions\": 5,\n262:     \"resolvedQuestions\": 0,\n263:     \"carr