ve children favor scoped, on-demand loading: no keyword match confirms artifact and intent before loading anything, and full inventory is explicit-only. Child fallbacks first request child-specific discriminators, then load a thin route map that points to one needed concern; this makes a child hint useful only after a candidate child is already ranked. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:207-214] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:69-124] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:21-38] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:21-35]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:55-101\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9, 207-214\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:51-124\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16, 64-145\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:15-38\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:15-35\",\n        \"command output: `wc -c` payload-size comparison\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-3b751ae37ebf\",\n      \"text\": \"An unconditional child-specific hint before ranking a candidate: each inspected child asks for information that presupposes its own domain, so it cannot resolve a genuine zero-signal hub request. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:81-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:105-124]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"3b751ae37ebf\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-98b360fee718\",\n      \"text\": \"Committed sources provide byte-size proxies, not a token budget or route-accuracy experiment; they cannot establish an exact numerical minimum payload.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"98b360fee718\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-18ffba478699\",\n      \"text\": \"The existing shared quick reference is not a neutral fallback-menu specimen, so its size cannot be treated as the target card size. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:64-145]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"18ffba478699\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-d3becd5e13cc\",\n      \"text\": \"Unconditional full-registry injection as the null fallback: it includes routing-adjacent metadata and all child surfaces, while the hub contract already separates classification from entry resolution. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-95]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"d3becd5e13cc\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n    }\n  ],\n  \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n  \"rejectedPatternIndex\": {\n    \"maxEntries\": 100,\n    \"fuzzyThreshold\": 0.85,\n    \"entries\": []\n  },\n  \"rejectedPatternWarnings\": [],\n  \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n  \"minIdeaObservations\": 2,\n  \"observedIdeas\": [],\n  \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n  \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n  \"graphConvergenceScore\": 0,\n  \"graphDecision\": null,\n  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n  \"divergence\": {\n    \"started\": [],\n    \"completed\": [],\n    \"failed\": [],\n    \"overrides\": [],\n    \"saturatedDirections\": [],\n    \"remainingFrontier\": [],\n    \"currentFocus\": \"\",\n    \"activePivotId\": null,\n    \"activeSourceIteration\": null\n  },\n  \"metrics\": {\n    \"iterationsCompleted\": 1,\n    \"openQuestions\": 5,\n    \"resolvedQuestions\": 0,\n    \"carriedForwardOpenQuestions\": 0,\n    \"keyFindings\": 4,\n    \"rejectedPatterns\": 0,\n    \"suppressedCandidates\": 0,\n    \"observedIdeas\": 0,\n    \"promotedIdeas\": 0,\n    \"suppressedIdeas\": 0,\n    \"convergenceScore\": 0.88,\n    \"coverageBySources\": {\n      \"code\": 11,\n      \"other\": 9\n    },\n    \"completedPivots\": 0,\n    \"failedPivots\": 0,\n    \"pivotOverrides\": 0\n  },\n  \"corruptionWarnings\": [],\n  \"inboxPath\": \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/inbox.jsonl\",\n  \"inboxWarnings\": [],\n  \"status\": \"INITIALIZED\",\n  \"advisoryEvents\": []\n}","lineStart":120,"lineEnd":284,"totalLines":284,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1784314517581,"end":1784314517585}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_06a0c11066223256016a5a7a9573908191b351bec76e1877c2"}},"id":"prt_f716ed8490014DR05qX6dxyXRj","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c8ffeulTMP4nVP9BJov","messageID":"msg_f716eadf9001BOTBvPmxjp6nD6"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784314517624,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c8ffeulTMP4nVP9BJov","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6sCi6JULHNYrgvLKfDUmKw5P","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/research.md","limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/research.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Progressive Research — terra-max Lineage\n2: \n3: ## Iteration 1: Minimum Useful Null-Hub Helper\n4: \n5: - The current null-hub path defers and asks for workflow mode, target component, inputs, and validation expectations, but its configured default resource is a quality/optimizer quick reference rather than a neutral cross-mode helper. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:77-97] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-14] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16]\n6: - Full-registry loading and unconditional child hints are not minimum default payloads; source topology instead supports a compact card with conditional child hints after ranking. Exact routing benefit and token floor remain unmeasured. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:207-214] [INFERENCE: based on the committed source topology and payload-size comparison]\n\n(End of file - total 6 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Progressive Research — terra-max Lineage\n\n## Iteration 1: Minimum Useful Null-Hub Helper\n\n- The current null-hub path defers and asks for workflow mode, target component, inputs, and validation expectations, but its configured default resource is a quality/optimizer quick reference rather than a neutral cross-mode helper. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:77-97] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-14] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16]\n- Full-registry loading and unconditional child hints are not minimum default payloads; source topology instead supports a compact card with conditional child hints after ranking. Exact routing benefit and token floor remain unmeasured. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:207-214] [INFERENCE: based on the committed source topology and payload-size comparison]","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/research.md","text":"# Progressive Research — terra-max Lineage\n\n## Iteration 1: Minimum Useful Null-Hub Helper\n\n- The current null-hub path defers and asks for workflow mode, target component, inputs, and validation expectations, but its configured default resource is a quality/optimizer quick reference rather than a neutral cross-mode helper. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:77-97] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-14] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16]\n- Full-registry loading and unconditional child hints are not minimum default payloads; source topology instead supports a compact card with conditional child hints after ranking. Exact routing benefit and token floor remain unmeasured. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:207-214] [INFERENCE: based on the committed source topology and payload-size comparison]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":6,"totalLines":6,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/research.md","time":{"start":1784314517621,"end":1784314517623}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_06a0c11066223256016a5a7a95739c8191b4fb5fc91d0e8076"}},"id":"prt_f716ed850001kceoQf6IAB9gVA","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c8ffeulTMP4nVP9BJov","messageID":"msg_f716eadf9001BOTBvPmxjp6nD6"}}
