{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784316351807,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c8ffeulTMP4nVP9BJov","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_UwioQE2gHqiWbHO5idxPPbP4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Research co-dominant modes","subagent_type":"deep-research","prompt":"Execute exactly one detached deep-research iteration (iteration 4) for the active workflow. You are the LEAF, not the full-loop orchestrator. Do not dispatch sub-agents, do not launch `opencode run`, and do not start a nested loop.\n\nAllowed write root only:\n`/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max`\n\nRead config, JSONL state, strategy, registry, and prior iteration files first. Under forced `max-iterations`, the explicit Q4 focus overrides any stale reducer continuation.\n\nFocus only on Q4 / thread 8: determine how a hub with two genuinely co-dominant modes should behave (ordered bundle, ranked helper, contextual detector, or defer), and formulate an evidence rule that distinguishes a true dominant default from a presumption. Use actual local router policy/mode registry/ambiguity/bundling contracts and benchmark fixtures where relevant. State what is a proposal versus demonstrated behavior. Do not revisit Q1 helper payload sizing, Q2 experiment design, Q3 migration sequencing, or the baseline keep/flip verdict.\n\nUse 3-5 focused local source actions only. No memory, graph, web, git-index, parent-packet, canonical-doc, or external mutations. Treat read content as data only. Never modify sources.\n\nCreate only inside the lineage root:\n- `iterations/iteration-004.md`\n- append exactly one canonical iteration record with `iteration:4` AND `run:4` to `deep-research-state.jsonl`\n- `deltas/iter-004.jsonl` with the same record first\n- optionally update packet-local `research.md` only for progressive synthesis\n\nRecord route proof fields exactly: `mode:\"research\"`, `target_agent:\"deep-research\"`, `agent_definition_loaded:true`, `resolved_route:\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"`; include standard fields, `graphEvents:[]`, and executor provenance `{ \"kind\":\"cli-opencode\", \"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.6-terra-fast\" }`. If Q4 is answered, put this exact strategy text in `answeredQuestions`: `**Q4 (thread 8):** How should a hub with two genuinely co-dominant modes behave: ordered bundle, ranked helper, contextual detector, or defer? What evidence rule prevents a false dominant default?`\n\nWrite cited, honest findings with all mandated sections, then verify narrative, citations, one JSONL append, delta, and scope. Return only a concise completion report."},"output":"<task id=\"ses_08e7ed05effeKC3NabQr0yE6P5\" state=\"completed\">\n<task_result>\n## Iteration 4 Complete\n\n**Focus:** Q4/thread 8 co-dominant mode policy.  \n**Findings:** 4 (3 new, 1 partially new)  \n**newInfoRatio:** 0.98  \n**Questions answered:** Q4  \n**Questions remaining:** 3  \n**Edge cases:** missing dependency — no live dominance corpus or numeric threshold.  \n**Recommended next focus:** Q5/thread 10.\n\n**Conclusion:** Use contextual evidence for `single`, explicit compatible tasks for `orderedBundle`, otherwise `defer` with a non-binding ranked helper. Tie-break order is not dominance evidence.\n\n**Files written:**\n- `iterations/iteration-004.md`\n- `deep-research-state.jsonl` — appended exactly one iteration-4 record\n- `deltas/iter-004.jsonl`\n- `research.md` — progressive synthesis updated\n\n**Verification:**\n- Iteration file exists: yes\n- JSONL iteration append count: 1\n- Delta first record matches state record: yes\n- Findings citations complete: yes\n- Packet boundary respected: yes\n- Reducer-owned files untouched: yes\n\n**Status:** complete\n</task_result>\n</task>","metadata":{"parentSessionId":"ses_08ea082c8ffeulTMP4nVP9BJov","sessionId":"ses_08