replacement contracts and benchmark assertions keep a null hub discoverable without recreating hidden auto-default bias?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"**Q5 (thread 10):** If `defaultMode` currently anchors hub identity or catch-all scoring, what exact replacement contracts and benchmark assertions keep a null hub discoverable without recreating hidden auto-default bias?\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"Inferring identity or catch-all scoring from the defaultMode property name\",\"Treating the existing route-gold runner as proof that proposed telemetry anti-bias assertions already exist\"],\"focusTrack\":\"null-hub-identity-anti-bias-contract\",\"edgeCase\":\"ambiguous-input\",\"toolsUsed\":[\"skill\",\"Read\",\"Glob\",\"Grep\",\"Bash\",\"apply_patch\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356,456-480,538-702\",\".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,196-208,246-298\",\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35\",\"command: Glob .opencode/skills/**/*router*.cjs\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-17T19:30:16Z\",\"durationMs\":300000,\"graphEvents\":[],\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.6-terra-fast\"}}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":5,\"kind\":\"confirmed-boundary\",\"text\":\"In the inspected replay, defaultMode affects only post-selection defaultApplied telemetry, not scores, workflowMode, packet, or backendKind.\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":5,\"kind\":\"proposal\",\"text\":\"Add null-hub defer/helper contracts and Z/W/A plus non-null-default mutation controls to route-gold before any policy change.\"}","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/deltas/iter-005.jsonl","text":"{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":5,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"run\":5,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Q5/thread 10 — defaultMode identity/catch-all boundary and null-hub replacement contracts\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.85,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Two findings add new code-level boundary and explicit anti-bias contracts; two refine prior policy/benchmark evidence, plus a simplicity bonus for reducing Q5 to testable invariants.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"**Q5 (thread 10):** If `defaultMode` currently anchors hub identity or catch-all scoring, what exact replacement contracts and benchmark assertions keep a null hub discoverable without recreating hidden auto-default bias?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"**Q5 (thread 10):** If `defaultMode` currently anchors hub identity or catch-all scoring, what exact replacement contracts and benchmark assertions keep a null hub discoverable without recreating hidden auto-default bias?\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"Inferring identity or catch-all scoring from the defaultMode property name\",\"Treating the existing route-gold runner as proof that proposed telemetry anti-bias assertions already exist\"],\"focusTrack\":\"null-hub-identity-anti-bias-contract\",\"edgeCase\":\"ambiguous-input\",\"toolsUsed\":[\"skill\",\"Read\",\"Glob\",\"Grep\",\"Bash\",\"apply_patch\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356,456-480,538-702\",\".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,196-208,246-298\",\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35\",\"command: Glob .opencode/skills/**/*router*.cjs\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-17T19:30:16Z\",\"durationMs\":300000,\"graphEvents\":[],\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.6-terra-fast\"}}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":5,\"kind\":\"confirmed-boundary\",\"text\":\"In the inspected replay, defaultMode affects only post-selection defaultApplied telemetry, not scores, workflowMode, packet, or backendKind.\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":5,\"kind\":\"proposal\",\"text\":\"Add null-hub defer/helper contracts and Z/W/A plus non-null-default mutation controls to route-gold before any policy change.\"}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":3,"totalLines":3,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/deltas/iter-005.jsonl","time":{"start":1784316777225,"end":1784316777228}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_007c1b05cb509631016a5a8368edf481918504c9635355a826"}},"id":"prt_f719152ed001CjZEYxaEYMCm7R","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c8ffeulTMP4nVP9BJov","messageID":"msg_f71912a86001NIbyrBUmqcYI1J"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784316777318,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c8ffeulTMP4nVP9BJov","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_0j9gmVqyz2moNQx05q7Jlbpd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/research.md","limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/research.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Progressive Research — terra-max Lineage\n2: \n3: ## Iteration 1: Minimum Useful Null-Hub Helper\n4: \n5: - The current null-hub path defers and asks for workflow mode, target component, inputs, and validation expectations, but its configured default resource is a quality/optimizer quick reference rather than a neutral cross-mode helper. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:77-97] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-14] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16]\n6: - Full-registry loading and unconditional child hints are not minimum default payloads; source topology instead supports a compact card with conditional child hints after ranking. Exact routing benefit and token floor remain unmeasured. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:207-214] [INFERENCE: based on the committed source topology and payload-size comparison]\n7: \n8: ## Iteration 2: Controlled Null-Hub Disambiguation\n9: \n10: - The replay seam makes a null-hub abstention observable (`defaultApplied: false`, `deferReason: no-mode-scored`) and separately resolves a weak `argument-hint` signal to `create-command`; these are the deterministic Z/W controls. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356] [SOURCE: command output: local node routeSkillResources replay for three fixtures]\n11: - A contradictory, single-choice two-mode prompt must be evaluated in live mode as well as replay: score `single|orderedBundle|defer`, wrong-mode selection, retained candidates, clarification adequacy, alias-order invariance, and resource leakage against blinded gold. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-97] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-206] [INFERENCE: based on the replay/live measurement split]\n12: \n13: ## Iteration 3: Safe `defaultMode` Migration and Rollback\n14: \n15: - A replayed `defaultApplied` signal is a policy-observation seam, not proof that live routing loaded a candidate child: use D5, enforced route gold, topology-digest stability, and then a bounded private-gold live trace before promotion. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356,643-702] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:246-298]\n16: - Freeze baseline gold, alter one `routerPolicy.defaultMode` field at a time, retain non-targeted weak/contradictory fixtures as invariants, and restore that field plus rerun the unchanged corpus on a hard-gate or private-gold regression. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:503-513] [INFERENCE: single-variable change preserves attribution and rollback evidence]\n17: \n18: ## Iteration 4: Co-Dominant Modes and Dominance Evidence\n19: \n20: - Current policy reserves `orderedBundle` for clearly separate intents and `defer` for unclear or contradictory ones; the `tieBreak` order is not proof that either tied mode is semantically dominant. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-97]\n21: - Proposed rule: contextual evidence may produce `single`; explicitly requested compatible tasks may produce `orderedBundle`; otherwise defer with a non-binding ranked helper. A default is demonstrated only by null-held, independently private-golded counterfactual evidence that survives paraphrase/alias-order/context variants and the hub route-gold/D5 gates. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-208,246-298,301-363] [INFERENCE: current contracts do not encode a dominance threshold or contextual detector]\n22: \n23: ## Iteration 5: Null-Hub Identity and Anti-Bias Contracts\n24: \n25: - Confirmed: the replay scores only signal-derived intents and derives `workflowMode`, `packet`, and `backendKind` from selected modes. Its only `defaultMode` read computes post-selection `defaultApplied`, so it does not currently anchor catch-all scoring or mode identity. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:456-480]\n26: - Proposed: preserve discoverability through a neutral defer/helper contract and make a non-null default fail a policy lint or Z/W/A route-gold invariants; do not let fallback metadata synthesize a mode, packet, backend, alias, score, or child resource. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:65-89,196-208,246-298] [INFERENCE: explicit anti-implicit-selection tests preserve the observed separation]\n\n(End of file - total 26 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Progressive Research — terra-max Lineage\n\n## Iteration 1: Minimum Useful Null-Hub Helper\n\n- The current null-hub path defers and asks for workflow mode, target component, inputs, and validation expectations, but its configured default resource is a quality/optimizer quick reference rather than a neutral cross-mode helper. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:77-97] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-14] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16]\n- Full-registry loading and unconditional child hints are not minimum default payloads; source topology instead supports a compact card with conditional child hints after ranking. Exact routing benefit and token floor remain unmeasured. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:207-214] [INFERENCE: based on the committed source topology and payload-size comparison]\n\n## Iteration 2: Controlled Null-Hub Disambiguation\n\n- The replay seam makes a null-hub abstention observable (`defaultApplied: false`, `deferReason: no-mode-scored`) and separately resolves a weak `argument-hint` signal to `create-command`; these are the deterministic Z/W controls. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356] [SOURCE: command output: local node routeSkillResources replay for three fixtures]\n- A contradictory, single-choice two-mode prompt must be evaluated in live mode as well as replay: score `single|orderedBundle|defer`, wrong-mode selection, retained candidates, clarification adequacy, alias-order invariance, and resource leakage against blinded gold. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-97] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-206] [INFERENCE: based on the replay/live measurement split]\n\n## Iteration 3: Safe `defaultMode` Migration and Rollback\n\n- A replayed `defaultApplied` signal is a policy-observation seam, not proof that live routing loaded a candidate child: use D5, enforced route gold, topology-digest stability, and then a bounded private-gold live trace before promotion. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356,643-702] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:246-298]\n- Freeze baseline gold, alter one `routerPolicy.defaultMode` field at a time, retain non-targeted weak/contradictory fixtures as invariants, and restore that field plus rerun the unchanged corpus on a hard-gate or private-gold regression. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:503-513] [INFERENCE: single-variable change preserves attribution and rollback evidence]\n\n## Iteration 4: Co-Dominant Modes and Dominance Evidence\n\n- Current policy reserves `orderedBundle` for clearly separate intents and `defer` for unclear or contradictory ones; the `tieBreak` order is not proof that either tied mode is semantically dominant. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-97]","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/research.md","text":"# Progressive Research — terra-max Lineage\n\n## Iteration 1: Minimum Useful Null-Hub Helper\n\n- The current null-hub path defers and asks for workflow mode, target component, inputs, and validation expectations, but its configured default resource is a quality/optimizer quick reference rather than a neutral cross-mode helper. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:77-97] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-14] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16]\n- Full-registry loading and unconditional child hints are not minimum default payloads; source topology instead supports a compact card with conditional child hints after ranking. Exact routing benefit and token floor remain unmeasured. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:207-214] [INFERENCE: based on the committed source topology and payload-size comparison]\n\n## Iteration 2: Controlled Null-Hub Disambiguation\n\n- The replay seam makes a null-hub abstention observable (`defaultApplied: false`, `deferReason: no-mode-scored`) and separately resolves a weak `argument-hint` signal to `create-command`; these are the deterministic Z/W controls. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356] [SOURCE: command output: local node routeSkillResources replay for three fixtures]\n- A contradictory, single-choice two-mode prompt must be evaluated in live mode as well as replay: score `single|orderedBundle|defer`, wrong-mode selection, retained candidates, clarification adequacy, alias-order invariance, and resource leakage against blinded gold. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-97] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-206] [INFERENCE: based on the replay/live measurement split]\n\n## Iteration 3: Safe `defaultMode` Migration and Rollback\n\n- A replayed `defaultApplied` signal is a policy-observation seam, not proof that live routing loaded a candidate child: use D5, enforced route gold, topology-digest stability, and then a bounded private-gold live trace before promotion. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356,643-702] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:246-298]\n- Freeze baseline gold, alter one `routerPolicy.defaultMode` field at a time, retain non-targeted weak/contradictory fixtures as invariants, and restore that field plus rerun the unchanged corpus on a hard-gate or private-gold regression. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:503-513] [INFERENCE: single-variable change preserves attribution and rollback evidence]\n\n## Iteration 4: Co-Dominant Modes and Dominance Evidence\n\n- Current policy reserves `orderedBundle` for clearly separate intents and `defer` for unclear or contradictory ones; the `tieBreak` order is not proof that either tied mode is semantically dominant. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-97]\n- Proposed rule: contextual evidence may produce `single`; explicitly requested compatible tasks may produce `orderedBundle`; otherwise defer with a non-binding ranked helper. A default is demonstrated only by null-held, independently private-golded counterfactual evidence that survives paraphrase/alias-order/context variants and the hub route-gold/D5 gates. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-208,246-298,301-363] [INFERENCE: current contracts do not encode a dominance threshold or contextual detector]\n\n## Iteration 5: Null-Hub Identity and Anti-Bias Contracts\n\n- Confirmed: the replay scores only signal-derived intents and derives `workflowMode`, `packet`, and `backendKind` from selected modes. Its only `defaultMode` read computes post-selection `defaultApplied`, so it does not currently anchor catch-all scoring or mode identity. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:456-480]\n- Proposed: preserve discoverability through a neutral defer/helper contract and make a non-null default fail a policy lint or Z/W/A route-gold invariants; do not let fallback metadata synthesize a mode, packet, backend, alias, score, or child resource. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:65-89,196-208,246-298] [INFERENCE: explicit anti-implicit-selection tests preserve the observed separation]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":26,"totalLines":26,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/research.md","time":{"start":1784316777315,"end":1784316777317}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_007c1b05cb509631016a5a8368edfc819194ef87d5efc589ae"}},"id":"prt_f7191530b001neATzy52MQUmPO","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c8ffeulTMP4nVP9BJov","messageID":"msg_f71912a86001NIbyrBUmqcYI1J"}}
