m arbitrary mode picking on a null hub, including zero-signal, weak-signal, and adversarially ambiguous requests?\",\n25:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n26:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n27:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n28:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n29:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n30:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": null,\n31:       \"resolved\": false\n32:     },\n33:     {\n34:       \"id\": \"question-3-q3-thread-4-what-safe-migration-and-rollback-sequence-could-flip-proposed-defaul\",\n35:       \"inboxId\": null,\n36:       \"text\": \"**Q3 (thread 4):** What safe migration and rollback sequence could flip proposed defaults while detecting regressions before live routing behavior is broadly affected?\",\n37:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n38:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n39:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n40:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n41:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n42:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": 3,\n43:       \"resolved\": true\n44:     },\n45:     {\n46:       \"id\": \"question-4-q4-thread-8-how-should-a-hub-with-two-genuinely-co-dominant-modes-behave-ordered\",\n47:       \"inboxId\": null,\n48:       \"text\": \"**Q4 (thread 8):** How should a hub with two genuinely co-dominant modes behave: ordered bundle, ranked helper, contextual detector, or defer? What evidence rule prevents a false dominant default?\",\n49:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n50:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n51:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n52:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n53:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n54:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": 4,\n55:       \"resolved\": true\n56:     },\n57:     {\n58:       \"id\": \"question-5-q5-thread-10-if-defaultmode-currently-anchors-hub-identity-or-catch-all-scoring-\",\n59:       \"inboxId\": null,\n60:       \"text\": \"**Q5 (thread 10):** If `defaultMode` currently anchors hub identity or catch-all scoring, what exact replacement contracts and benchmark assertions keep a null hub discoverable without recreating hidden auto-default bias?\",\n61:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n62:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n63:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n64:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n65:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n66:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": 5,\n67:       \"resolved\": true\n68:     }\n69:   ],\n70:   \"openQuestions\": [\n71:     {\n72:       \"id\": \"question-1-q1-thread-1-when-a-null-hub-defers-what-routing-helper-payload-actually-improves\",\n73:       \"inboxId\": null,\n74:       \"text\": \"**Q1 (thread 1):** When a null hub defers, what routing-helper payload actually improves live routing: a full mode registry, a compressed disambiguation card, or a child hint? What measurable tradeoff establishes the minimum useful payload?\",\n75:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n76:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n77:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n78:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n79:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n80:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n81:     },\n82:     {\n83:       \"id\": \"question-2-q2-thread-3-what-controlled-experiment-would-distinguish-clean-model-disambiguat\",\n84:       \"inboxId\": null,\n85:       \"text\": \"**Q2 (thread 3):** What controlled experiment would distinguish clean model disambiguation from arbitrary mode picking on a null hub, including zero-signal, weak-signal, and adversarially ambiguous requests?\",\n86:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n87:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n88:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n89:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n90:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n91:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n92:     }\n93:   ],\n94:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n95:     {\n96:       \"id\": \"question-3-q3-thread-4-what-safe-migration-and-rollback-sequence-could-flip-proposed-defaul\",\n97:       \"inboxId\": null,\n98:       \"text\": \"**Q3 (thread 4):** What safe migration and rollback sequence could flip proposed defaults while detecting regressions before live routing behavior is broadly affected?\",\n99:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n100:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n101:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n102:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n103:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n104:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": 3\n105:     },\n106:     {\n107:       \"id\": \"question-4-q4-thread-8-how-should-a-hub-with-two-genuinely-co-dominant-modes-behave-ordered\",\n108:       \"inboxId\": null,\n109:       \"text\": \"**Q4 (thread 8):** How should a hub with two genuinely co-dominant modes behave: ordered bundle, ranked helper, contextual detector, or defer? What evidence rule prevents a false dominant default?\",\n110:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n111:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n112:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n113:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n114:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n115:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": 4\n116:     },\n117:     {\n118:       \"id\": \"question-5-q5-thread-10-if-defaultmode-currently-anchors-hub-identity-or-catch-all-scoring-\",\n119:       \"inboxId\": null,\n120:       \"text\": \"**Q5 (thread 10):** If `defaultMode` currently anchors hub identity or catch-all scoring, what exact replacement contracts and benchmark assertions keep a null hub discoverable without recreating hidden auto-default bias?\",\n121:       \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n122:       \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n123:       \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n124:       \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n125:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n126:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": 5\n127:     }\n128:   ],\n129:   \"carriedForwardOpenQuestions\": [],\n130:   \"uncoveredQuestions\": [\n131:     \"**Q1 (thread 1):** When a null hub defers, what routing-helper payload actually improves live routing: a full mode registry, a compressed disambiguation card, or a child hint? What measurable tradeoff establishes the minimum useful payload?\",\n132:     \"**Q2 (thread 3):** What controlled experiment would distinguish clean model disambiguation from arbitrary mode picking on a null hub, including zero-signal, weak-signal, and adversarially ambiguous requests?\"\n133:   ],\n134:   \"keyFindings\": [\n135:     {\n136:       \"id\": \"finding-1-4-the-committed-payload-sizes-make-indiscriminate-helper-loading-hard-to-justify-q\",\n137:       \"text\": \"The committed payload sizes make indiscriminate helper loading hard to justify: `quick_reference.md` is 14,132 bytes, the full registry is 10,515 bytes, `hub-router.json` is 5,937 bytes, and the two representative child route maps are 3,942 and 3,804 bytes. The minimum plausible improvement is therefore a newly generated compressed disambiguation card: defer reason; zero to two ranked candidate mode labels with one discriminating alias each; the four hub confirmation fields; and a child hint only for an already-ranked candidate. This is a proposal, not a measured token floor. [SOURCE: command output: wc -c .opencode/skills/sk-doc/{mode-registry.json,hub-router.json,shared/references/quick_reference.md,create-command/references/README.md,create-quality-control/references/README.md}] [INFERENCE: based on the source topology and payload-size comparison above]\",\n138:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n139:       \"sources\": [\n140:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160\",\n141:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n142:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:55-101\",\n143:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9, 207-214\",\n144:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92\",\n145:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:51-124\",\n146:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16, 64-145\",\n147:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:15-38\",\n148:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:15-35\",\n149:         \"command output: `wc -c` payload-size comparison\"\n150:       ]\n151:     },\n152:     {\n153:       \"id\": \"finding-1-1-the-full-mode-registry-json-is-not-a-minimal-null-state-helper-it-carries-all-12\",\n154:       \"text\": \"The full `mode-registry.json` is not a minimal null-state helper: it carries all 12 workflow entries, including packet identity, command, aliases, tool surfaces, and advisor metadata. The hub instead classifies with `hub-router.json`, then resolves the matching registry entry only after a mode is selected. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-95]\",\n155:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n156:       \"sources\": [\n157:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160\",\n158:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n159:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:55-101\",\n160:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9, 207-214\",\n161:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92\",\n162:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:51-124\",\n163:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16, 64-145\",\n164:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:15-38\",\n165:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:15-35\",\n166:         \"command output: `wc -c` payload-size comparison\"\n167:       ]\n168:     },\n169:     {\n170:       \"id\": \"finding-1-2-the-live-null-hub-behavior-already-has-a-small-semantic-contract-with-low-confid\",\n171:       \"text\": \"The live null-hub behavior already has a small *semantic* contract: with low confidence, contradiction, or no winning mode under `defaultMode: null`, it loads `shared/references/quick_reference.md` and asks for workflow mode, target component, inputs, and validation expectations. But the configured default resource is a quality/optimizer cheat sheet, not a cross-mode choice card. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-14] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:77-97] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:64-145]\",\n172:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n173:       \"sources\": [\n174:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160\",\n175:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n176:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:55-101\",\n177:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9, 207-214\",\n178:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92\",\n179:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:51-124\",\n180:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16, 64-145\",\n181:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:15-38\",\n182:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:15-35\",\n183:         \"command output: `wc -c` payload-size comparison\"\n184:       ]\n185:     },\n186:     {\n187:       \"id\": \"finding-1-3-the-second-layer-router-and-representative-children-favor-scoped-on-demand-loadi\",\n188:       \"text\": \"The second-layer router and representative children favor scoped, on-demand loading: no keyword match confirms artifact and intent before loading anything, and full inventory is explicit-only. Child fallbacks first request child-specific discriminators, then load a thin route map that points to one needed concern; this makes a child hint useful only after a candidate child is already ranked. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:207-214] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:69-124] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:21-38] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:21-35]\",\n189:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n190:       \"sources\": [\n191:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160\",\n192:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n193:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:55-101\",\n194:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9, 207-214\",\n195:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92\",\n196:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:51-124\",\n197:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16, 64-145\",\n198:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:15-38\",\n199:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:15-35\",\n200:         \"command output: `wc -c` payload-size comparison\"\n201:       ]\n202:     },\n203:     {\n204:       \"id\": \"finding-2-2-a-local-three-prompt-replay-supplies-stable-controls-for-the-first-two-strata-i-\",\n205:       \"text\": \"A local three-prompt replay supplies stable controls for the first two strata: `I need help with some documentation.` produced no intents, `defaultApplied: false`, and `deferReason: \\\"no-mode-scored\\\"`; `Please add an argument-hint to a command.` produced only `create-command` from the `argument-hint` alias. This distinguishes correct abstention from a weak but discriminating signal without changing hub sources. [SOURCE: command output: node router-replay.cjs module invocation for the three listed prompts] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:27,42]\",\n206:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2,\n207:       \"sources\": [\n208:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n209:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:45-101\",\n210:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356,456-480,538-702,709-728\",\n211:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-206\",\n212:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,47-50,73-88\",\n213:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/assets/skill_benchmark/fixtures/README.md:18-26,50-58\",\n214:         \"command output: local `node` invocation of `routeSkillResources` for zero-signal, weak-signal, and adversarial prompts\"\n215:       ]\n216:     },\n217:     {\n218:       \"id\": \"finding-2-3-the-adversarial-prompt-i-need-a-command-template-and-a-flowchart-but-only-one-ch\",\n219:       \"text\": \"The adversarial prompt `I need a command template and a flowchart, but only one; choose one.` tied `create-command` and `create-flowchart` in replay and surfaced `deferReason: \\\"ambiguous-multi-axis\\\"`, while the replay still returned candidate modes and flowchart resources. That is a useful mechanical baseline, but it cannot itself prove clean model behavior: replay selects scored keywords within the ambiguity delta and returns telemetry/resources, whereas the hub contract requires `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` when intent is contradictory. [SOURCE: command output: node router-replay.cjs module invocation for the three listed prompts] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:456-480,643-702] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-97]\",\n220:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2,\n221:       \"sources\": [\n222:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n223:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:45-101\",\n224:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356,456-480,538-702,709-728\",\n225:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-206\",\n226:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,47-50,73-88\",\n227:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/assets/skill_benchmark/fixtures/README.md:18-26,50-58\",\n228:         \"command output: local `node` invocation of `routeSkillResources` for zero-signal, weak-signal, and adversarial prompts\"\n229:       ]\n230:     },\n231:     {\n232:       \"id\": \"finding-2-4-the-controlled-experiment-should-use-matched-blinded-fixture-pairs-in-three-stra\",\n233:       \"text\": \"The controlled experiment should use matched, blinded fixture pairs in three strata: **Z** zero-signal prompts golded as `defer` with a discriminating clarification; **W** weak-signal prompts golded as one named mode; and **A** two-mode, “only one” prompts golded as `defer` retaining both candidates. Each A fixture needs an alias-order reversal and a paraphrase pair; a separate explicit-two-task prompt is the positive `orderedBundle` control. Measure exact outcome correctness (`single|orderedBundle|defer`), wrong-mode rate on Z/A, candidate-retention recall on A, clarification-discriminator adequacy, alias-order flip rate, and false-positive resource count. Run deterministic router replay as the mechanical control, then live dispatch with scorer-only gold to measure actual model behavior; the benchmark already runs replay before scoring, enables route-gold by default for hub skills, and reserves live dispatch for follow-on measurement. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-206] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,73-88] [INFERENCE: combining the replay telemetry seam, the null-hub contract, and the existing playbook's positive multi-intent control]\",\n234:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2,\n235:       \"sources\": [\n236:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n237:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:45-101\",\n238:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356,456-480,538-702,709-728\",\n239:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-206\",\n240:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,47-50,73-88\",\n241:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/assets/skill_benchmark/fixtures/README.md:18-26,50-58\",\n242:         \"command output: local `node` invocation of `routeSkillResources` for zero-signal, weak-signal, and adversarial prompts\"\n243:       ]\n244:     },\n245:     {\n246:       \"id\": \"finding-2-1-the-deterministic-replay-exposes-a-testable-null-hub-abstention-trace-it-reports\",\n247:       \"text\": \"The deterministic replay exposes a testable null-hub abstention trace: it reports `workflowMode`, `defaultApplied`, and `deferReason`; `defaultApplied` can only be true when no mode scored and the policy has a non-null default. The `sk-doc` policy sets `defaultMode` to `null`, so zero-signal fixtures can assert no automatic default separately from downstream response quality. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-13]\",\n248:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2,\n249:       \"sources\": [\n250:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n251:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:45-101\",\n252:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356,456-480,538-702,709-728\",\n253:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-206\",\n254:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,47-50,73-88\",\n255:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/assets/skill_benchmark/fixtures/README.md:18-26,50-58\",\n256:         \"command output: local `node` invocation of `routeSkillResources` for zero-signal, weak-signal, and adversarial prompts\"\n257:       ]\n258:     },\n259:     {\n260:       \"id\": \"finding-3-4-recommended-order-1-freeze-and-pass-the-baseline-corpus-2-produce-one-single-fie\",\n261:       \"text\": \"Recommended order: **1)** freeze and pass the baseline corpus; **2)** produce one single-field candidate and its explicit candidate fixture gold; **3)** rerun D5 plus route-gold replay; **4)** run only the bounded target scenarios in live trace mode with private/scorer-only evaluation; **5)** promote one hub at a time only when the candidate equals or improves the predeclared pass rate and cost envelope; **6)** observe the same telemetry after each promotion. Roll back immediately by restoring that one recorded `defaultMode` value and rerunning the unchanged baseline corpus if a hard benchmark block, topology drift, an invariant-fixture failure, an unplanned default application, or a live private-gold regression occurs. This applies the repository's established default-off/frozen-corpus rollout discipline without asserting that this hub already has a runtime canary switch. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:269-298] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:301-388] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:151-162] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:503-513] [INFERENCE: one-field promotion and restoration minimize affected routing surface and preserve a decisive rollback comparison]\",\n262:       \"addedAtIteration\": 3,\n263:       \"sources\": [\n264:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20\",\n265:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97\",\n266:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356, 643-702\",\n267:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20, 65-89, 174-206, 246-298, 301-388\",\n268:         \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:151-162, 503-513\"\n269:       ]\n270:     },\n271:     {\n272:       \"id\": \"finding-3-1-router-replay-supplies-necessary-observability-but-cannot-alone-prove-that-a-liv\",\n273:       \"text\": \"Router replay supplies necessary observability but cannot alone prove that a live route loaded a proposed default. Its hub telemetry marks `defaultApplied` only when no modes were selected and the policy value is non-null; the replay then continues to assemble resources from the unchanged selected-intent list. A candidate therefore needs a live, privately scored check after deterministic replay rather than treating `defaultApplied: true` as proof of the user-visible route. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:643-702]\",\n274:       \"addedAtIteration\": 3,\n275:       \"sources\": [\n276:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20\",\n277:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97\",\n278:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356, 643-702\",\n279:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20, 65-89, 174-206, 246-298, 301-388\",\n280:         \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:151-162, 503-513\"\n281:       ]\n282:     },\n283:     {\n284:       \"id\": \"finding-3-2-the-minimum-deterministic-evidence-gate-before-each-candidate-change-is-a-pass-t\",\n285:       \"text\": \"The minimum deterministic evidence gate before **each** candidate change is: (a) pass the D5 connectivity and hub-registry scan; (b) run the frozen target-owned playbook corpus with route gold explicitly enabled; and (c) retain the generated JSON/Markdown report plus the topology digest. D5 runs before dispatch, hub skills enable route gold by default, and either a structural/registry/route-gold block or a manifest change during scoring returns a failing process signal rather than merely a warning. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:65-89] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:246-298]\",\n286:       \"addedAtIteration\": 3,\n287:       \"sources\": [\n288:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20\",\n289:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97\",\n290:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356, 643-702\",\n291:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20, 65-89, 174-206, 246-298, 301-388\",\n292:         \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:151-162, 503-513\"\n293:       ]\n294:     },\n295:     {\n296:       \"id\": \"finding-3-3-use-two-immutable-fixture-views-preserve-the-current-baseline-gold-unchanged-the\",\n297:       \"text\": \"Use two immutable fixture views: preserve the current baseline gold unchanged, then add candidate-specific private gold for the intentional zero-signal behavior while retaining weak-signal and contradictory-intent invariants. Observe every candidate by fixture stratum through `workflowMode`, `matchedAliases`, `defaultApplied`, `deferReason`, packet, and backend-kind telemetry; a non-targeted default application, changed weak-mode route, or loss of contradictory-intent defer is a regression. The hub's policy keeps default, ambiguity, tie-break, outcomes, fallback resource, and bundle rules together, while its registry and hub router are synchronized projections, so changing more than one of those controls destroys causal attribution. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97] [INFERENCE: preserve baseline gold and isolate the candidate expectation so intentional change is distinguishable from collateral drift]\",\n298:       \"addedAtIteration\": 3,\n299:       \"sources\": [\n300:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20\",\n301:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97\",\n302:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356, 643-702\",\n303:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20, 65-89, 174-206, 246-298, 301-388\",\n304:         \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:151-162, 503-513\"\n305:       ]\n306:     },\n307:     {\n308:       \"id\": \"finding-4-2-demonstrated-contract-boundary-the-current-registry-defines-mode-identity-packet\",\n309:       \"text\": \"**Demonstrated contract boundary:** the current registry defines mode identity, packet/backend mapping, commands, aliases, and advisor metadata; the routing contract either defers low-confidence/contradictory/no-winner input or loads each already-resolved mode. Neither source defines a `rankedHelper`, a contextual-detector schema, or a dominance-measurement field. A ranked helper or contextual detector is consequently a proposal, not current hub behavior. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:5-15,17-163] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97]\",\n310:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4,\n311:       \"sources\": [\n312:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20\",\n313:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:5-15,17-163\",\n314:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97\",\n315:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,73-88\",\n316:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-208,246-298,301-363\"\n317:       ]\n318:     },\n319:     {\n320:       \"id\": \"finding-4-1-demonstrated-policy-behavior-sk-doc-assigns-single-only-to-one-dominant-intent-r\",\n321:       \"text\": \"**Demonstrated policy behavior:** `sk-doc` assigns `single` only to one dominant intent, reserves `orderedBundle` for clearly separate authoring intents, and uses `defer` for unclear or contradictory intent. Its configured default is `null`; the `tieBreak` is an ordered list, while the only explicit bundle rule is `create-skill` plus `create-quality-control`. An ordered tie-break is therefore deterministic ordering metadata, not demonstrated evidence that one candidate is semantically dominant. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-97] [INFERENCE: the policy defines order but no evidence or outcome field that converts tie-break position into dominance]\",\n322:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4,\n323:       \"sources\": [\n324:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20\",\n325:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:5-15,17-163\",\n326:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97\",\n327:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,73-88\",\n328:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-208,246-298,301-363\"\n329:       ]\n330:     },\n331:     {\n332:       \"id\": \"finding-4-3-fixture-evidence-is-conditional-not-a-default-proof-sd-007-treats-an-explicit-tw\",\n333:       \"text\": \"**Fixture evidence is conditional, not a default proof:** SD-007 treats an explicit two-task request as one where both candidates must be retained; its acceptance allows a union/combined route or an explicit disambiguation and rejects silently discarding either. That supports an ordered bundle only when the request independently asks for both compatible tasks. Its `DOC_QUALITY`/`FLOWCHART` labels are not current `workflowMode` identifiers, so the fixture needs a current-ID mapping before it is executable route gold; it does not demonstrate that a generic co-dominant score should auto-bundle or select a default. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,73-88] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-163] [INFERENCE: fixture labels differ from the registry’s current workflow-mode keys]\",\n334:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4,\n335:       \"sources\": [\n336:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20\",\n337:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:5-15,17-163\",\n338:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97\",\n339:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,73-88\",\n340:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-208,246-298,301-363\"\n341:       ]\n342:     },\n343:     {\n344:       \"id\": \"finding-4-4-proposal-decision-ladder-and-evidence-rule-run-a-contextual-detector-first-when-\",\n345:       \"text\": \"**Proposal — decision ladder and evidence rule:** run a contextual detector first; when it supplies a unique, predeclared discriminator, return `single`. If the prompt independently requests both compatible tasks and an explicit bundle rule supports their order, return `orderedBundle`. If two modes remain co-dominant, or the user requires one but supplies no discriminator, `defer` and show a ranked helper as a non-binding explanation rather than dispatching a mode. Treat a candidate as a true dominant default only after a current-ID, independently private-golded corpus keeps it the unique desired outcome with `defaultMode` held null during measurement, remains invariant under paraphrase/alias-order/context variants, preserves explicit bundle and contradictory-single-choice cases, and passes the hub route-gold/D5 gates; if that counterfactual evidence is absent, the default is a presumption and the correct outcome is `defer`. The inspected benchmark supplies deterministic route-gold enforcement and an opt-in, target-owned live outcome pass, but no numeric dominance threshold or completed live result. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-208,246-298,301-363] [INFERENCE: the ladder operationalizes the current three outcomes while preventing the fallback policy from supplying its own evidence]\",\n346:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4,\n347:       \"sources\": [\n348:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20\",\n349:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:5-15,17-163\",\n350:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97\",\n351:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,73-88\",\n352:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-208,246-298,301-363\"\n353:       ]\n354:     },\n355:     {\n356:       \"id\": \"finding-5-1-confirmed-defaultmode-does-not-enter-current-replay-scoring-or-mode-identity-sco\",\n357:       \"text\": \"**Confirmed — `defaultMode` does not enter current replay scoring or mode identity.** `scoreIntents()` derives scores solely from `intentSignals`, and `selectIntents()` retains only scored modes within the ambiguity delta. `buildHubRouteTelemetry()` derives `workflowMode`, `packet`, and `backendKind` from that selected-mode list before it computes `defaultApplied`; the sole `defaultMode` read is the post-selection boolean `selectedModes.length === 0 && policy.defaultMode != null`. Thus a non-null value is observed as telemetry, not inserted as a score, selected mode, packet, or backend identity. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:456-480] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:643-702]\",\n358:       \"addedAtIteration\": 5,\n359:       \"sources\": [\n360:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356, 456-480, 538-702\",\n361:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20, 65-89, 196-208, 246-298\",\n362:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35\",\n363:         \"command output: Glob `.opencode/skills/**/*router*.cjs` (identified `router-replay.cjs` as the relevant shared replay implementation)\"\n364:       ]\n365:     },\n366:     {\n367:       \"id\": \"finding-5-2-confirmed-the-sk-doc-policy-separates-the-null-default-from-discovery-signals-it\",\n368:       \"text\": \"**Confirmed — the `sk-doc` policy separates the null default from discovery signals.** Its policy declares `defaultMode: null`, while mode discovery is represented by independently weighted `routerSignals`; its documented outcomes reserve `defer` for unclear or contradictory input. `defaultResource` is a separate fallback-resource field, not a workflow-mode identifier. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35]\",\n369:       \"addedAtIteration\": 5,\n370:       \"sources\": [\n371:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356, 456-480, 538-702\",\n372:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20, 65-89, 196-208, 246-298\",\n373:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35\",\n374:         \"command output: Glob `.opencode/skills/**/*router*.cjs` (identified `router-replay.cjs` as the relevant shared replay implementation)\"\n375:       ]\n376:     },\n377:     {\n378:       \"id\": \"finding-5-3-confirmed-the-current-benchmark-has-a-suitable-enforcement-seam-but-not-a-demons\",\n379:       \"text\": \"**Confirmed — the current benchmark has a suitable enforcement seam but not a demonstrated anti-bias schema.** Hub skills enable route gold by default, D5 executes before scenarios, every authored-gold row is sent through `evaluateRouteGold`, and enforced structural/registry/route-gold failures return a non-zero exit code. The runner therefore provides the place to enforce null-hub invariants, but these sources do not demonstrate that its existing gold schema already checks the proposed telemetry fields below. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:65-89] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:196-208] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:246-298]\",\n380:       \"addedAtIteration\": 5,\n381:       \"sources\": [\n382:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356, 456-480, 538-702\",\n383:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20, 65-89, 196-208, 246-298\",\n384:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35\",\n385:         \"command output: Glob `.opencode/skills/**/*router*.cjs` (identified `router-replay.cjs` as the relevant shared replay implementation)\"\n386:       ]\n387:     },\n388:     {\n389:       \"id\": \"finding-5-4-proposed-replacement-contracts-and-assertions-a-define-a-hubdefer-result-with-wo\",\n390:       \"text\": \"**Proposed replacement contracts and assertions:** (a) define a `HubDefer` result with `workflowMode: null`, scored `candidateModes`, `matchedAliases`, and a `deferReason`; `packet` and `backendKind` remain empty until a signal-selected mode exists; (b) replace any future catch-all default with a neutral `DiscoverabilityHelper` that asks one discriminating question and may describe the hub, but carries no mode id, child packet path, synthetic alias, or score; and (c) make `defaultMode` nullable only as a policy compatibility field, with `null` required for a null hub and any non-null value rejected by a static anti-implicit-selection check. Route-gold should then assert: **Z** zero-signal gives null mode, empty aliases/packet/backend, `defaultApplied: false`, and `no-mode-scored`; **W** weak-signal gives exactly its signal-selected mode and no default; **A** ambiguous input retains candidates while deferring and loads no child mode resource; and alias-order/paraphrase variants preserve Z/A abstention. A mutation control with a non-null `defaultMode` must fail the new policy lint or these invariants, so discoverability cannot silently become auto-dispatch. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:456-480] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:65-89] [INFERENCE: the proposal preserves the observed separation between scoring, identity, fallback, and benchmark enforcement while making a future regression fail explicitly]\",\n391:       \"addedAtIteration\": 5,\n392:       \"sources\": [\n393:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356, 456-480, 538-702\",\n394:         \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20, 65-89, 196-208, 246-298\",\n395:         \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35\",\n396:         \"command output: Glob `.opencode/skills/**/*router*.cjs` (identified `router-replay.cjs` as the relevant shared replay implementation)\"\n397:       ]\n398:     }\n399:   ],\n400:   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n401:     {\n402:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-3b751ae37ebf\",\n403:       \"text\": \"An unconditional child-specific hint before ranking a candidate: each inspected child asks for information that presupposes its own domain, so it cannot resolve a genuine zero-signal hub request. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:81-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:105-124]\",\n404:       \"contentHash\": \"3b751ae37ebf\",\n405:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n406:     },\n407:     {\n408:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-98b360fee718\",\n409:       \"text\": \"Committed sources provide byte-size proxies, not a token budget or route-accuracy experiment; they cannot establish an exact numerical minimum payload.\",\n410:       \"contentHash\": \"98b360fee718\",\n411:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n412:     },\n413:     {\n414:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-18ffba478699\",\n415:       \"text\": \"The existing shared quick reference is not a neutral fallback-menu specimen, so its size cannot be treated as the target card size. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:64-145]\",\n416:       \"contentHash\": \"18ffba478699\",\n417:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n418:     },\n419:     {\n420:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-d3becd5e13cc\",\n421:       \"text\": \"Unconditional full-registry injection as the null fallback: it includes routing-adjacent metadata and all child surfaces, while the hub contract already separates classification from entry resolution. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-95]\",\n422:       \"contentHash\": \"d3becd5e13cc\",\n423:       \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n424:     },\n425:     {\n426:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-cbb43bb0b455\",\n427:       \"text\": \"A single ambiguous fixture without alias-order and paraphrase counterparts cannot attribute a resulting pick to evidence rather than incidental ordering; use paired variants as the minimum adversarial unit. [INFERENCE: based on the equal-score replay result and the ordered hub tie-break policy]\",\n428:       \"contentHash\": \"cbb43bb0b455\",\n429:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n430:     },\n431:     {\n432:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-fb9b292474e5\",\n433:       \"text\": \"The legacy public/private fixture directory is supported only by explicit `--fixtures-dir` and is superseded by each skill's manual-testing playbook, so it is not the default seam for this experiment. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/assets/skill_benchmark/fixtures/README.md:18-26,50-58]\",\n434:       \"contentHash\": \"fb9b292474e5\",\n435:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n436:     },\n437:     {\n438:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-9a7ec723c9cc\",\n439:       \"text\": \"Treating deterministic replay alone as proof of model-level clean disambiguation: it records scored candidates and telemetry but does not grade the model's clarification or semantic handling of the “only one” constraint. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:456-480,643-702] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:84-86]\",\n440:       \"contentHash\": \"9a7ec723c9cc\",\n441:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n442:     },\n443:     {\n444:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-624efc4df3a3\",\n445:       \"text\": \"Treating the existing SD-007 multi-intent scenario as the adversarial fixture: its contract deliberately permits a combined route or an explicit disambiguation, so it cannot detect an arbitrary single pick where the user said only one mode is wanted. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,73-88]\",\n446:       \"contentHash\": \"624efc4df3a3\",\n447:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n448:     },\n449:     {\n450:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-72c280c6d752\",\n451:       \"text\": \"A multi-hub flip combined with changes to router signals, registry projections, fallback resources, or tie-break order: the resulting outcome cannot be attributed to the `defaultMode` change and cannot be cleanly rolled back. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97] [INFERENCE: coupled policy edits remove the single-variable comparison]\",\n452:       \"contentHash\": \"72c280c6d752\",\n453:       \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n454:     },\n455:     {\n456:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-7c8fa050e87f\",\n457:       \"text\": \"No inspected hub or benchmark contract defines a runtime `defaultMode` canary/percentage selector. Do not assume one exists; use a bounded candidate run and explicitly scoped live scenarios until such a control is authored. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:372-388] [INFERENCE: the inspected contracts expose a policy field and trace-mode selection, not a per-hub rollout selector]\",\n458:       \"contentHash\": \"7c8fa050e87f\",\n459:       \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n460:     },\n461:     {\n462:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-e48c64076271\",\n463:       \"text\": \"The inspected contracts do not set a numeric tolerance for live route-quality regression. Structural and route-gold failures are zero-tolerance gates; any live pass-rate or cost tolerance must be predeclared with the candidate rather than invented after observing results. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:289-298] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:503-513]\",\n464:       \"contentHash\": \"e48c64076271\",\n465:       \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n466:     },\n467:     {\n468:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-ac56d4049053\",\n469:       \"text\": \"Treating deterministic `defaultApplied` telemetry as proof that live dispatch selected or loaded the candidate child. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:342-356] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:643-702]\",\n470:       \"contentHash\": \"ac56d4049053\",\n471:       \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n472:     },\n473:     {\n474:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-83c94621ef64\",\n475:       \"text\": \"No inspected local contract supplies a numeric dominance threshold, a recorded contextual-detector result, or a live outcome corpus. Do not invent a percentage threshold or call a ranked helper current behavior. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:18-20,301-363] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:5-15]\",\n476:       \"contentHash\": \"83c94621ef64\",\n477:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n478:     },\n479:     {\n480:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-401ab114b48a\",\n481:       \"text\": \"SD-007 alone cannot establish a generic co-dominance rule because its acceptance deliberately permits either a combined route or explicit disambiguation for an explicit two-task prompt. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:73-88]\",\n482:       \"contentHash\": \"401ab114b48a\",\n483:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n484:     },\n485:     {\n486:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-7debf328ac9d\",\n487:       \"text\": \"Treating `routerPolicy.tieBreak` order or an already-configured `defaultMode` as proof of semantic dominance. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-13] [INFERENCE: both are policy controls, not independently scored user outcomes]\",\n488:       \"contentHash\": \"7debf328ac9d\",\n489:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n490:     },\n491:     {\n492:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-b9220242f5b6\",\n493:       \"text\": \"Treating every within-delta two-mode score as an ordered bundle. The policy and SD-007 distinguish explicit separate tasks from unclear or contradictory alternatives. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:8-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,73-88]\",\n494:       \"contentHash\": \"b9220242f5b6\",\n495:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n496:     },\n497:     {\n498:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-4f1fff99972f\",\n499:       \"text\": \"Using SD-007’s legacy intent labels as current executable route gold without mapping them to current registry identifiers. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:2-13] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-163]\",\n500:       \"contentHash\": \"4f1fff99972f\",\n501:       \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n502:     },\n503:     {\n504:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-3a91d327f17f\",\n505:       \"text\": \"`defaultApplied` alone cannot prove a mode was selected or a child was loaded: it is true only for zero selected modes with a non-null policy value, while runtime identity arrays are derived from the selected modes. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:325-355]\",\n506:       \"contentHash\": \"3a91d327f17f\",\n507:       \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n508:     },\n509:     {\n510:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-5efacc51b64e\",\n511:       \"text\": \"A neutral fallback resource must not be treated as a covert mode: the hub policy models `defaultResource` separately from `defaultMode` and `routerSignals`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35]\",\n512:       \"contentHash\": \"5efacc51b64e\",\n513:       \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n514:     },\n515:     {\n516:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-1ded37706e16\",\n517:       \"text\": \"Inferring that `defaultMode` anchors runtime identity or catch-all scoring from its field name: in the inspected replay it is read only after selection to compute telemetry. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:456-480]\",\n518:       \"contentHash\": \"1ded37706e16\",\n519:       \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n520:     },\n521:     {\n522:       \"id\": \"ruled-out-f15bd44ffcca\",\n523:       \"text\": \"Treating the current route-gold runner as proof that it already enforces the proposed null-hub telemetry assertions: the inspected runner invokes route gold and hard-gates its verdict, but does not itself establish those new expectation fields. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:196-208] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:289-298]\",\n524:       \"contentHash\": \"f15bd44ffcca\",\n525:       \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n526:     }\n527:   ],\n528:   \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n529:   \"rejectedPatternIndex\": {\n530:     \"maxEntries\": 100,\n531:     \"fuzzyThreshold\": 0.85,\n532:     \"entries\": []\n533:   },\n534:   \"rejectedPatternWarnings\": [],\n535:   \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n536:   \"minIdeaObservations\": 2,\n537:   \"observedIdeas\": [],\n538:   \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n539:   \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n540:   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n541:   \"graphConvergenceScore\": 0,\n542:   \"graphDecision\": null,\n543:   \"graphBlockers\": [],\n544:   \"divergence\": {\n545:     \"started\": [],\n546:     \"completed\": [],\n547:     \"failed\": [],\n548:     \"overrides\": [],\n549:     \"saturatedDirections\": [],\n550:     \"remainingFrontier\": [],\n551:     \"currentFocus\": \"\",\n552:     \"activePivotId\": null,\n553:     \"activeSourceIteration\": null\n554:   },\n555:   \"metrics\": {\n556:     \"iterationsCompleted\": 5,\n557:     \"openQuestions\": 2,\n558:     \"resolvedQuestions\": 3,\n559:     \"carriedForwardOpenQuestions\": 0,\n560:     \"keyFindings\": 20,\n561:     \"rejectedPatterns\": 0,\n562:     \"suppressedCandidates\": 0,\n563:     \"observedIdeas\": 0,\n564:     \"promotedIdeas\": 0,\n565:     \"suppressedIdeas\": 0,\n566:     \"convergenceScore\": 0.85,\n567:     \"coverageBySources\": {\n568:       \"code\": 36,\n569:       \"other\": 13\n570:     },\n571:     \"completedPivots\": 0,\n572:     \"failedPivots\": 0,\n573:     \"pivotOverrides\": 0\n574:   },\n575:   \"corruptionWarnings\": [],\n576:   \"inboxPath\": \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/inbox.jsonl\",\n577:   \"inboxWarnings\": [],\n578:   \"status\": \"INITIALIZED\",\n579:   \"advisoryEvents\": []\n580: }\n\n(End of file - total 580 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-terra-max-1784313510669-wn3vsj\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"terminalStop\": null,\n  \"keyQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-1-q1-thread-1-when-a-null-hub-defers-what-routing-helper-payload-actually-improves\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"**Q1 (thread 1):** When a null hub defers, what routing-helper payload actually improves live routing: a full mode registry, a compressed disambiguation card, or a child hint? What measurable tradeoff establishes the minimum useful payload?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null,\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/findings-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-terra-max-1784313510669-wn3vsj\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"terminalStop\": null,\n  \"keyQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-1-q1-thread-1-when-a-null-hub-defers-what-routing-helper-payload-actually-improves\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"**Q1 (thread 1):** When a null hub defers, what routing-helper payload actually improves live routing: a full mode registry, a compressed disambiguation card, or a child hint? What measurable tradeoff establishes the minimum useful payload?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null,\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-2-q2-thread-3-what-controlled-experiment-would-distinguish-clean-model-disambiguat\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"**Q2 (thread 3):** What controlled experiment would distinguish clean model disambiguation from arbitrary mode picking on a null hub, including zero-signal, weak-signal, and adversarially ambiguous requests?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null,\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-3-q3-thread-4-what-safe-migration-and-rollback-sequence-could-flip-proposed-defaul\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"**Q3 (thread 4):** What safe migration and rollback sequence could flip proposed defaults while detecting regressions before live routing behavior is broadly affected?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": 3,\n      \"resolved\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-4-q4-thread-8-how-should-a-hub-with-two-genuinely-co-dominant-modes-behave-ordered\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"**Q4 (thread 8):** How should a hub with two genuinely co-dominant modes behave: ordered bundle, ranked helper, contextual detector, or defer? What evidence rule prevents a false dominant default?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": 4,\n      \"resolved\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-5-q5-thread-10-if-defaultmode-currently-anchors-hub-identity-or-catch-all-scoring-\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"**Q5 (thread 10):** If `defaultMode` currently anchors hub identity or catch-all scoring, what exact replacement contracts and benchmark assertions keep a null hub discoverable without recreating hidden auto-default bias?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": 5,\n      \"resolved\": true\n    }\n  ],\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-1-q1-thread-1-when-a-null-hub-defers-what-routing-helper-payload-actually-improves\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"**Q1 (thread 1):** When a null hub defers, what routing-helper payload actually improves live routing: a full mode registry, a compressed disambiguation card, or a child hint? What measurable tradeoff establishes the minimum useful payload?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-2-q2-thread-3-what-controlled-experiment-would-distinguish-clean-model-disambiguat\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"**Q2 (thread 3):** What controlled experiment would distinguish clean model disambiguation from arbitrary mode picking on a null hub, including zero-signal, weak-signal, and adversarially ambiguous requests?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n    }\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-3-q3-thread-4-what-safe-migration-and-rollback-sequence-could-flip-proposed-defaul\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"**Q3 (thread 4):** What safe migration and rollback sequence could flip proposed defaults while detecting regressions before live routing behavior is broadly affected?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-4-q4-thread-8-how-should-a-hub-with-two-genuinely-co-dominant-modes-behave-ordered\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"**Q4 (thread 8):** How should a hub with two genuinely co-dominant modes behave: ordered bundle, ranked helper, contextual detector, or defer? What evidence rule prevents a false dominant default?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-5-q5-thread-10-if-defaultmode-currently-anchors-hub-identity-or-catch-all-scoring-\",\n      \"inboxId\": null,\n      \"text\": \"**Q5 (thread 10):** If `defaultMode` currently anchors hub identity or catch-all scoring, what exact replacement contracts and benchmark assertions keep a null hub discoverable without recreating hidden auto-default bias?\",\n      \"origin\": \"legacy-import\",\n      \"source\": \"key-questions\",\n      \"injectedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"promotedQuestionId\": null,\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": 5\n    }\n  ],\n  \"carriedForwardOpenQuestions\": [],\n  \"uncoveredQuestions\": [\n    \"**Q1 (thread 1):** When a null hub defers, what routing-helper payload actually improves live routing: a full mode registry, a compressed disambiguation card, or a child hint? What measurable tradeoff establishes the minimum useful payload?\",\n    \"**Q2 (thread 3):** What controlled experiment would distinguish clean model disambiguation from arbitrary mode picking on a null hub, including zero-signal, weak-signal, and adversarially ambiguous requests?\"\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-1-4-the-committed-payload-sizes-make-indiscriminate-helper-loading-hard-to-justify-q\",\n      \"text\": \"The committed payload sizes make indiscriminate helper loading hard to justify: `quick_reference.md` is 14,132 bytes, the full registry is 10,515 bytes, `hub-router.json` is 5,937 bytes, and the two representative child route maps are 3,942 and 3,804 bytes. The minimum plausible improvement is therefore a newly generated compressed disambiguation card: defer reason; zero to two ranked candidate mode labels with one discriminating alias each; the four hub confirmation fields; and a child hint only for an already-ranked candidate. This is a proposal, not a measured token floor. [SOURCE: command output: wc -c .opencode/skills/sk-doc/{mode-registry.json,hub-router.json,shared/references/quick_reference.md,create-command/references/README.md,create-quality-control/references/README.md}] [INFERENCE: based on the source topology and payload-size comparison above]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:55-101\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9, 207-214\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:51-124\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16, 64-145\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:15-38\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:15-35\",\n        \"command output: `wc -c` payload-size comparison\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-1-1-the-full-mode-registry-json-is-not-a-minimal-null-state-helper-it-carries-all-12\",\n      \"text\": \"The full `mode-registry.json` is not a minimal null-state helper: it carries all 12 workflow entries, including packet identity, command, aliases, tool surfaces, and advisor metadata. The hub instead classifies with `hub-router.json`, then resolves the matching registry entry only after a mode is selected. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-95]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:55-101\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9, 207-214\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:51-124\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16, 64-145\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:15-38\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:15-35\",\n        \"command output: `wc -c` payload-size comparison\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-1-2-the-live-null-hub-behavior-already-has-a-small-semantic-contract-with-low-confid\",\n      \"text\": \"The live null-hub behavior already has a small *semantic* contract: with low confidence, contradiction, or no winning mode under `defaultMode: null`, it loads `shared/references/quick_reference.md` and asks for workflow mode, target component, inputs, and validation expectations. But the configured default resource is a quality/optimizer cheat sheet, not a cross-mode choice card. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-14] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:77-97] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:64-145]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:55-101\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9, 207-214\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:51-124\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16, 64-145\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:15-38\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:15-35\",\n        \"command output: `wc -c` payload-size comparison\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-1-3-the-second-layer-router-and-representative-children-favor-scoped-on-demand-loadi\",\n      \"text\": \"The second-layer router and representative children favor scoped, on-demand loading: no keyword match confirms artifact and intent before loading anything, and full inventory is explicit-only. Child fallbacks first request child-specific discriminators, then load a thin route map that points to one needed concern; this makes a child hint useful only after a candidate child is already ranked. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:207-214] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:69-124] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:21-38] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:21-35]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:55-101\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/smart_routing.md:8-9, 207-214\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:56-92\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:51-124\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16, 64-145\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/README.md:15-38\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/references/README.md:15-35\",\n        \"command output: `wc -c` payload-size comparison\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-2-2-a-local-three-prompt-replay-supplies-stable-controls-for-the-first-two-strata-i-\",\n      \"text\": \"A local three-prompt replay supplies stable controls for the first two strata: `I need help with some documentation.` produced no intents, `defaultApplied: false`, and `deferReason: \\\"no-mode-scored\\\"`; `Please add an argument-hint to a command.` produced only `create-command` from the `argument-hint` alias. This distinguishes correct abstention from a weak but discriminating signal without changing hub sources. [SOURCE: command output: node router-replay.cjs module invocation for the three listed prompts] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:27,42]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 2,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:45-101\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356,456-480,538-702,709-728\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-206\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,47-50,73-88\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/assets/skill_benchmark/fixtures/README.md:18-26,50-58\",\n        \"command output: local `node` invocation of `routeSkillResources` for zero-signal, weak-signal, and adversarial prompts\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-2-3-the-adversarial-prompt-i-need-a-command-template-and-a-flowchart-but-only-one-ch\",\n      \"text\": \"The adversarial prompt `I need a command template and a flowchart, but only one; choose one.` tied `create-command` and `create-flowchart` in replay and surfaced `deferReason: \\\"ambiguous-multi-axis\\\"`, while the replay still returned candidate modes and flowchart resources. That is a useful mechanical baseline, but it cannot itself prove clean model behavior: replay selects scored keywords within the ambiguity delta and returns telemetry/resources, whereas the hub contract requires `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` when intent is contradictory. [SOURCE: command output: node router-replay.cjs module invocation for the three listed prompts] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:456-480,643-702] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-97]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 2,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:45-101\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356,456-480,538-702,709-728\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-206\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,47-50,73-88\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/assets/skill_benchmark/fixtures/README.md:18-26,50-58\",\n        \"command output: local `node` invocation of `routeSkillResources` for zero-signal, weak-signal, and adversarial prompts\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-2-4-the-controlled-experiment-should-use-matched-blinded-fixture-pairs-in-three-stra\",\n      \"text\": \"The controlled experiment should use matched, blinded fixture pairs in three strata: **Z** zero-signal prompts golded as `defer` with a discriminating clarification; **W** weak-signal prompts golded as one named mode; and **A** two-mode, “only one” prompts golded as `defer` retaining both candidates. Each A fixture needs an alias-order reversal and a paraphrase pair; a separate explicit-two-task prompt is the positive `orderedBundle` control. Measure exact outcome correctness (`single|orderedBundle|defer`), wrong-mode rate on Z/A, candidate-retention recall on A, clarification-discriminator adequacy, alias-order flip rate, and false-positive resource count. Run deterministic router replay as the mechanical control, then live dispatch with scorer-only gold to measure actual model behavior; the benchmark already runs replay before scoring, enables route-gold by default for hub skills, and reserves live dispatch for follow-on measurement. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-206] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,73-88] [INFERENCE: combining the replay telemetry seam, the null-hub contract, and the existing playbook's positive multi-intent control]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 2,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:45-101\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356,456-480,538-702,709-728\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-206\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,47-50,73-88\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/assets/skill_benchmark/fixtures/README.md:18-26,50-58\",\n        \"command output: local `node` invocation of `routeSkillResources` for zero-signal, weak-signal, and adversarial prompts\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-2-1-the-deterministic-replay-exposes-a-testable-null-hub-abstention-trace-it-reports\",\n      \"text\": \"The deterministic replay exposes a testable null-hub abstention trace: it reports `workflowMode`, `defaultApplied`, and `deferReason`; `defaultApplied` can only be true when no mode scored and the policy has a non-null default. The `sk-doc` policy sets `defaultMode` to `null`, so zero-signal fixtures can assert no automatic default separately from downstream response quality. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-13]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 2,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-50\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:45-101\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356,456-480,538-702,709-728\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-206\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,47-50,73-88\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/assets/skill_benchmark/fixtures/README.md:18-26,50-58\",\n        \"command output: local `node` invocation of `routeSkillResources` for zero-signal, weak-signal, and adversarial prompts\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-3-4-recommended-order-1-freeze-and-pass-the-baseline-corpus-2-produce-one-single-fie\",\n      \"text\": \"Recommended order: **1)** freeze and pass the baseline corpus; **2)** produce one single-field candidate and its explicit candidate fixture gold; **3)** rerun D5 plus route-gold replay; **4)** run only the bounded target scenarios in live trace mode with private/scorer-only evaluation; **5)** promote one hub at a time only when the candidate equals or improves the predeclared pass rate and cost envelope; **6)** observe the same telemetry after each promotion. Roll back immediately by restoring that one recorded `defaultMode` value and rerunning the unchanged baseline corpus if a hard benchmark block, topology drift, an invariant-fixture failure, an unplanned default application, or a live private-gold regression occurs. This applies the repository's established default-off/frozen-corpus rollout discipline without asserting that this hub already has a runtime canary switch. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:269-298] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:301-388] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:151-162] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:503-513] [INFERENCE: one-field promotion and restoration minimize affected routing surface and preserve a decisive rollback comparison]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 3,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356, 643-702\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20, 65-89, 174-206, 246-298, 301-388\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:151-162, 503-513\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-3-1-router-replay-supplies-necessary-observability-but-cannot-alone-prove-that-a-liv\",\n      \"text\": \"Router replay supplies necessary observability but cannot alone prove that a live route loaded a proposed default. Its hub telemetry marks `defaultApplied` only when no modes were selected and the policy value is non-null; the replay then continues to assemble resources from the unchanged selected-intent list. A candidate therefore needs a live, privately scored check after deterministic replay rather than treating `defaultApplied: true` as proof of the user-visible route. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:643-702]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 3,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356, 643-702\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20, 65-89, 174-206, 246-298, 301-388\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:151-162, 503-513\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-3-2-the-minimum-deterministic-evidence-gate-before-each-candidate-change-is-a-pass-t\",\n      \"text\": \"The minimum deterministic evidence gate before **each** candidate change is: (a) pass the D5 connectivity and hub-registry scan; (b) run the frozen target-owned playbook corpus with route gold explicitly enabled; and (c) retain the generated JSON/Markdown report plus the topology digest. D5 runs before dispatch, hub skills enable route gold by default, and either a structural/registry/route-gold block or a manifest change during scoring returns a failing process signal rather than merely a warning. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:65-89] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:246-298]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 3,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356, 643-702\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20, 65-89, 174-206, 246-298, 301-388\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:151-162, 503-513\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-3-3-use-two-immutable-fixture-views-preserve-the-current-baseline-gold-unchanged-the\",\n      \"text\": \"Use two immutable fixture views: preserve the current baseline gold unchanged, then add candidate-specific private gold for the intentional zero-signal behavior while retaining weak-signal and contradictory-intent invariants. Observe every candidate by fixture stratum through `workflowMode`, `matchedAliases`, `defaultApplied`, `deferReason`, packet, and backend-kind telemetry; a non-targeted default application, changed weak-mode route, or loss of contradictory-intent defer is a regression. The hub's policy keeps default, ambiguity, tie-break, outcomes, fallback resource, and bundle rules together, while its registry and hub router are synchronized projections, so changing more than one of those controls destroys causal attribution. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97] [INFERENCE: preserve baseline gold and isolate the candidate expectation so intentional change is distinguishable from collateral drift]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 3,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356, 643-702\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20, 65-89, 174-206, 246-298, 301-388\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:151-162, 503-513\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-4-2-demonstrated-contract-boundary-the-current-registry-defines-mode-identity-packet\",\n      \"text\": \"**Demonstrated contract boundary:** the current registry defines mode identity, packet/backend mapping, commands, aliases, and advisor metadata; the routing contract either defers low-confidence/contradictory/no-winner input or loads each already-resolved mode. Neither source defines a `rankedHelper`, a contextual-detector schema, or a dominance-measurement field. A ranked helper or contextual detector is consequently a proposal, not current hub behavior. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:5-15,17-163] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:5-15,17-163\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,73-88\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-208,246-298,301-363\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-4-1-demonstrated-policy-behavior-sk-doc-assigns-single-only-to-one-dominant-intent-r\",\n      \"text\": \"**Demonstrated policy behavior:** `sk-doc` assigns `single` only to one dominant intent, reserves `orderedBundle` for clearly separate authoring intents, and uses `defer` for unclear or contradictory intent. Its configured default is `null`; the `tieBreak` is an ordered list, while the only explicit bundle rule is `create-skill` plus `create-quality-control`. An ordered tie-break is therefore deterministic ordering metadata, not demonstrated evidence that one candidate is semantically dominant. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-97] [INFERENCE: the policy defines order but no evidence or outcome field that converts tie-break position into dominance]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:5-15,17-163\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,73-88\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-208,246-298,301-363\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-4-3-fixture-evidence-is-conditional-not-a-default-proof-sd-007-treats-an-explicit-tw\",\n      \"text\": \"**Fixture evidence is conditional, not a default proof:** SD-007 treats an explicit two-task request as one where both candidates must be retained; its acceptance allows a union/combined route or an explicit disambiguation and rejects silently discarding either. That supports an ordered bundle only when the request independently asks for both compatible tasks. Its `DOC_QUALITY`/`FLOWCHART` labels are not current `workflowMode` identifiers, so the fixture needs a current-ID mapping before it is executable route gold; it does not demonstrate that a generic co-dominant score should auto-bundle or select a default. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,73-88] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-163] [INFERENCE: fixture labels differ from the registry’s current workflow-mode keys]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:5-15,17-163\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,73-88\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-208,246-298,301-363\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-4-4-proposal-decision-ladder-and-evidence-rule-run-a-contextual-detector-first-when-\",\n      \"text\": \"**Proposal — decision ladder and evidence rule:** run a contextual detector first; when it supplies a unique, predeclared discriminator, return `single`. If the prompt independently requests both compatible tasks and an explicit bundle rule supports their order, return `orderedBundle`. If two modes remain co-dominant, or the user requires one but supplies no discriminator, `defer` and show a ranked helper as a non-binding explanation rather than dispatching a mode. Treat a candidate as a true dominant default only after a current-ID, independently private-golded corpus keeps it the unique desired outcome with `defaultMode` held null during measurement, remains invariant under paraphrase/alias-order/context variants, preserves explicit bundle and contradictory-single-choice cases, and passes the hub route-gold/D5 gates; if that counterfactual evidence is absent, the default is a presumption and the correct outcome is `defer`. The inspected benchmark supplies deterministic route-gold enforcement and an opt-in, target-owned live outcome pass, but no numeric dominance threshold or completed live result. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-208,246-298,301-363] [INFERENCE: the ladder operationalizes the current three outcomes while preventing the fallback policy from supplying its own evidence]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:5-15,17-163\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,73-88\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20,65-89,174-208,246-298,301-363\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-5-1-confirmed-defaultmode-does-not-enter-current-replay-scoring-or-mode-identity-sco\",\n      \"text\": \"**Confirmed — `defaultMode` does not enter current replay scoring or mode identity.** `scoreIntents()` derives scores solely from `intentSignals`, and `selectIntents()` retains only scored modes within the ambiguity delta. `buildHubRouteTelemetry()` derives `workflowMode`, `packet`, and `backendKind` from that selected-mode list before it computes `defaultApplied`; the sole `defaultMode` read is the post-selection boolean `selectedModes.length === 0 && policy.defaultMode != null`. Thus a non-null value is observed as telemetry, not inserted as a score, selected mode, packet, or backend identity. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:456-480] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:643-702]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 5,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356, 456-480, 538-702\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20, 65-89, 196-208, 246-298\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35\",\n        \"command output: Glob `.opencode/skills/**/*router*.cjs` (identified `router-replay.cjs` as the relevant shared replay implementation)\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-5-2-confirmed-the-sk-doc-policy-separates-the-null-default-from-discovery-signals-it\",\n      \"text\": \"**Confirmed — the `sk-doc` policy separates the null default from discovery signals.** Its policy declares `defaultMode: null`, while mode discovery is represented by independently weighted `routerSignals`; its documented outcomes reserve `defer` for unclear or contradictory input. `defaultResource` is a separate fallback-resource field, not a workflow-mode identifier. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 5,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356, 456-480, 538-702\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20, 65-89, 196-208, 246-298\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35\",\n        \"command output: Glob `.opencode/skills/**/*router*.cjs` (identified `router-replay.cjs` as the relevant shared replay implementation)\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-5-3-confirmed-the-current-benchmark-has-a-suitable-enforcement-seam-but-not-a-demons\",\n      \"text\": \"**Confirmed — the current benchmark has a suitable enforcement seam but not a demonstrated anti-bias schema.** Hub skills enable route gold by default, D5 executes before scenarios, every authored-gold row is sent through `evaluateRouteGold`, and enforced structural/registry/route-gold failures return a non-zero exit code. The runner therefore provides the place to enforce null-hub invariants, but these sources do not demonstrate that its existing gold schema already checks the proposed telemetry fields below. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:65-89] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:196-208] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:246-298]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 5,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356, 456-480, 538-702\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20, 65-89, 196-208, 246-298\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35\",\n        \"command output: Glob `.opencode/skills/**/*router*.cjs` (identified `router-replay.cjs` as the relevant shared replay implementation)\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"finding-5-4-proposed-replacement-contracts-and-assertions-a-define-a-hubdefer-result-with-wo\",\n      \"text\": \"**Proposed replacement contracts and assertions:** (a) define a `HubDefer` result with `workflowMode: null`, scored `candidateModes`, `matchedAliases`, and a `deferReason`; `packet` and `backendKind` remain empty until a signal-selected mode exists; (b) replace any future catch-all default with a neutral `DiscoverabilityHelper` that asks one discriminating question and may describe the hub, but carries no mode id, child packet path, synthetic alias, or score; and (c) make `defaultMode` nullable only as a policy compatibility field, with `null` required for a null hub and any non-null value rejected by a static anti-implicit-selection check. Route-gold should then assert: **Z** zero-signal gives null mode, empty aliases/packet/backend, `defaultApplied: false`, and `no-mode-scored`; **W** weak-signal gives exactly its signal-selected mode and no default; **A** ambiguous input retains candidates while deferring and loads no child mode resource; and alias-order/paraphrase variants preserve Z/A abstention. A mutation control with a non-null `defaultMode` must fail the new policy lint or these invariants, so discoverability cannot silently become auto-dispatch. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:456-480] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:65-89] [INFERENCE: the proposal preserves the observed separation between scoring, identity, fallback, and benchmark enforcement while making a future regression fail explicitly]\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 5,\n      \"sources\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356, 456-480, 538-702\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20, 65-89, 196-208, 246-298\",\n        \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35\",\n        \"command output: Glob `.opencode/skills/**/*router*.cjs` (identified `router-replay.cjs` as the relevant shared replay implementation)\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-3b751ae37ebf\",\n      \"text\": \"An unconditional child-specific hint before ranking a candidate: each inspected child asks for information that presupposes its own domain, so it cannot resolve a genuine zero-signal hub request. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:81-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-quality-control/SKILL.md:105-124]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"3b751ae37ebf\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-98b360fee718\",\n      \"text\": \"Committed sources provide byte-size proxies, not a token budget or route-accuracy experiment; they cannot establish an exact numerical minimum payload.\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"98b360fee718\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-18ffba478699\",\n      \"text\": \"The existing shared quick reference is not a neutral fallback-menu specimen, so its size cannot be treated as the target card size. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:2-16] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/quick_reference.md:64-145]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"18ffba478699\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-d3becd5e13cc\",\n      \"text\": \"Unconditional full-registry injection as the null fallback: it includes routing-adjacent metadata and all child surfaces, while the hub contract already separates classification from entry resolution. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-160] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:80-95]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"d3becd5e13cc\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-cbb43bb0b455\",\n      \"text\": \"A single ambiguous fixture without alias-order and paraphrase counterparts cannot attribute a resulting pick to evidence rather than incidental ordering; use paired variants as the minimum adversarial unit. [INFERENCE: based on the equal-score replay result and the ordered hub tie-break policy]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"cbb43bb0b455\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-fb9b292474e5\",\n      \"text\": \"The legacy public/private fixture directory is supported only by explicit `--fixtures-dir` and is superseded by each skill's manual-testing playbook, so it is not the default seam for this experiment. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/assets/skill_benchmark/fixtures/README.md:18-26,50-58]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"fb9b292474e5\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-9a7ec723c9cc\",\n      \"text\": \"Treating deterministic replay alone as proof of model-level clean disambiguation: it records scored candidates and telemetry but does not grade the model's clarification or semantic handling of the “only one” constraint. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:456-480,643-702] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:84-86]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"9a7ec723c9cc\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-624efc4df3a3\",\n      \"text\": \"Treating the existing SD-007 multi-intent scenario as the adversarial fixture: its contract deliberately permits a combined route or an explicit disambiguation, so it cannot detect an arbitrary single pick where the user said only one mode is wanted. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,73-88]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"624efc4df3a3\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-72c280c6d752\",\n      \"text\": \"A multi-hub flip combined with changes to router signals, registry projections, fallback resources, or tie-break order: the resulting outcome cannot be attributed to the `defaultMode` change and cannot be cleanly rolled back. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:48-97] [INFERENCE: coupled policy edits remove the single-variable comparison]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"72c280c6d752\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-7c8fa050e87f\",\n      \"text\": \"No inspected hub or benchmark contract defines a runtime `defaultMode` canary/percentage selector. Do not assume one exists; use a bounded candidate run and explicitly scoped live scenarios until such a control is authored. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:372-388] [INFERENCE: the inspected contracts expose a policy field and trace-mode selection, not a per-hub rollout selector]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"7c8fa050e87f\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-e48c64076271\",\n      \"text\": \"The inspected contracts do not set a numeric tolerance for live route-quality regression. Structural and route-gold failures are zero-tolerance gates; any live pass-rate or cost tolerance must be predeclared with the candidate rather than invented after observing results. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:289-298] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:503-513]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"e48c64076271\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-ac56d4049053\",\n      \"text\": \"Treating deterministic `defaultApplied` telemetry as proof that live dispatch selected or loaded the candidate child. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:342-356] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:643-702]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"ac56d4049053\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-83c94621ef64\",\n      \"text\": \"No inspected local contract supplies a numeric dominance threshold, a recorded contextual-detector result, or a live outcome corpus. Do not invent a percentage threshold or call a ranked helper current behavior. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:18-20,301-363] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:5-15]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"83c94621ef64\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-401ab114b48a\",\n      \"text\": \"SD-007 alone cannot establish a generic co-dominance rule because its acceptance deliberately permits either a combined route or explicit disambiguation for an explicit two-task prompt. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:73-88]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"401ab114b48a\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-7debf328ac9d\",\n      \"text\": \"Treating `routerPolicy.tieBreak` order or an already-configured `defaultMode` as proof of semantic dominance. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-13] [INFERENCE: both are policy controls, not independently scored user outcomes]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"7debf328ac9d\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-b9220242f5b6\",\n      \"text\": \"Treating every within-delta two-mode score as an ordered bundle. The policy and SD-007 distinguish explicit separate tasks from unclear or contradictory alternatives. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:8-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:37-42,73-88]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"b9220242f5b6\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-4f1fff99972f\",\n      \"text\": \"Using SD-007’s legacy intent labels as current executable route gold without mapping them to current registry identifiers. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/unknown_fallback/ambiguous_multi_intent.md:2-13] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/mode-registry.json:17-163]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"4f1fff99972f\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-3a91d327f17f\",\n      \"text\": \"`defaultApplied` alone cannot prove a mode was selected or a child was loaded: it is true only for zero selected modes with a non-null policy value, while runtime identity arrays are derived from the selected modes. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:325-355]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"3a91d327f17f\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-5efacc51b64e\",\n      \"text\": \"A neutral fallback resource must not be treated as a covert mode: the hub policy models `defaultResource` separately from `defaultMode` and `routerSignals`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/hub-router.json:4-35]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"5efacc51b64e\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-1ded37706e16\",\n      \"text\": \"Inferring that `defaultMode` anchors runtime identity or catch-all scoring from its field name: in the inspected replay it is read only after selection to compute telemetry. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:315-356] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs:456-480]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"1ded37706e16\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ruled-out-f15bd44ffcca\",\n      \"text\": \"Treating the current route-gold runner as proof that it already enforces the proposed null-hub telemetry assertions: the inspected runner invokes route gold and hard-gates its verdict, but does not itself establish those new expectation fields. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:196-208] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:289-298]\",\n      \"contentHash\": \"f15bd44ffcca\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n    }\n  ],\n  \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n  \"rejectedPatternIndex\": {\n    \"maxEntries\": 100,\n    \"fuzzyThreshold\": 0.85,\n    \"entries\": []\n  },\n  \"rejectedPatternWarnings\": [],\n  \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n  \"minIdeaObservations\": 2,\n  \"observedIdeas\": [],\n  \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n  \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n  \"graphConvergenceScore\": 0,\n  \"graphDecision\": null,\n  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n  \"divergence\": {\n    \"started\": [],\n    \"completed\": [],\n    \"failed\": [],\n    \"overrides\": [],\n    \"saturatedDirections\": [],\n    \"remainingFrontier\": [],\n    \"currentFocus\": \"\",\n    \"activePivotId\": null,\n    \"activeSourceIteration\": null\n  },\n  \"metrics\": {\n    \"iterationsCompleted\": 5,\n    \"openQuestions\": 2,\n    \"resolvedQuestions\": 3,\n    \"carriedForwardOpenQuestions\": 0,\n    \"keyFindings\": 20,\n    \"rejectedPatterns\": 0,\n    \"suppressedCandidates\": 0,\n    \"observedIdeas\": 0,\n    \"promotedIdeas\": 0,\n    \"suppressedIdeas\": 0,\n    \"convergenceScore\": 0.85,\n    \"coverageBySources\": {\n      \"code\": 36,\n      \"other\": 13\n    },\n    \"completedPivots\": 0,\n    \"failedPivots\": 0,\n    \"pivotOverrides\": 0\n  },\n  \"corruptionWarnings\": [],\n  \"inboxPath\": \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/inbox.jsonl\",\n  \"inboxWarnings\": [],\n  \"status\": \"INITIALIZED\",\n  \"advisoryEvents\": []\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":580,"totalLines":580,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/terra-max/findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1784316802601,"end":1784316802604}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02a3a494b9639e27016a5a838254ec81919962e39f6b5a502d"}},"id":"prt_f7191b5dc001ujVXzvWZ4CJoCA","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c8ffeulTMP4nVP9BJov","messageID":"msg_f719179650016k2EXFs6sy8DYO"}}
